Dear Cortez family,

A reminder of two items on the calendar, plus a couple of housekeeping notes as we head into the holiday stretch.

First, there is an early release day for all grades at the end of November. Dismissal is at half past eleven. Please confirm your pickup arrangement with the office by the twentieth of November. Families we do not hear from will get a call to the primary guardian that morning. If someone other than a parent is collecting your child, that name must be on the approved pickup list on file, so let us know in advance and we will add them.

Second, the winter concert is in December in the parish hall in the evening. Chloe's fourth grade class is performing. Liam's seventh grade is not in the choir this year. Doors open thirty minutes before the performance and seating is first come. Students in the concert should wear school uniform, white top and dark bottoms.

Tuition of four hundred fifty debits on the first as usual. Any financial aid adjustments must be filed by the fifteenth of December. If your billing information has changed, please update it through the parent portal before the first so the debit clears cleanly.

A few last reminders. Report cards for the first trimester go home the week after the concert. The office is closed for the Thanksgiving break from Wednesday afternoon through the following Monday. And flu season is here, please keep children home with a fever and send a note when they return.

As always, thank you for being part of the Holy Name community. Please reach out with any questions.

